experiment 14
compartion operator overloading 
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Aim:

To write a C++ program to overload the comparison operator (==) to compare two objects based on their data values.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Algorithm:

1. Start the program.
2. Create a class with required data members (e.g., int a).
3. Write a constructor to initialize the object.
4. Overload the comparison operator (==) inside the class.
5. In the overloaded operator:
Compare the data of the current object (this->a) with the passed object (obj.a).
Return true if equal, otherwise false.
6. In main():
Create two objects with values.
Compare them using the overloaded operator (obj1 == obj2).
7. Display whether the objects are equal or not.
8. End the program.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Source Code :

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

class Compare {
    int value;

public:
    // Constructor
    Compare(int v = 0) {
        value = v;
    }

    // Overloading == operator
    bool operator == (const Compare &obj) {
        return value == obj.value;
    }

    // Display values
    void display() {
        cout << "Value = " << value << endl;
    }
};

int main() {
    Compare c1(10);
    Compare c2(10);
    Compare c3(20);

    cout << "Comparing c1 and c2: ";
    if (c1 == c2)
        cout << "Equal" << endl;
    else
        cout << "Not Equal" << endl;

    cout << "Comparing c1 and c3: ";
    if (c1 == c3)
        cout << "Equal" << endl;
    else
        cout << "Not Equal" << endl;

    return 0;
}
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Sample Output:

Comparing c1 and c2: Equal
Comparing c1 and c3: Not Equal.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Result:

The program successfully overloads the comparison operator (==) and compares two objects based on their data values. The output correctly displays whether the objects are equal or not.


